<leg:bodytext>
<p>
<text>(Legal Profession Act 2004)</text></p>
<p>
<blockquote>
<p indent="none"><text><emph typestyle="bf">Legal costs &#x2014; your right to know</emph></text></p>
<p indent="none"><text>You have the right to:</text>
<l>
<li><lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>negotiate a costs agreement with us</text></p></li>
<li><lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>receive a bill of costs from us</text></p></li>
<li><lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>request an itemised bill of costs after you receive a lump sum bill from us</text></p></li>
<li><lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>request written reports about the progress of your matter and the costs incurred in your matter</text></p></li>
<li><lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>apply for costs to be assessed within 12 months if you are unhappy with our costs</text></p></li>
<li><lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>apply for the costs agreement to be set aside</text></p></li>
<li><lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>accept or reject any offer we make for an interstate costs law to apply to your matter</text></p></li>
<li><lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>notify us that you require an interstate costs law to apply to your matter</text></p></li></l></p>
<p indent="none"><text>For more information about your rights, please read the fact sheet titled <emph typestyle="it">Legal Costs &#x2014; your right to know</emph>. You can ask us for a copy, or obtain it from your local law society or law institute (or download it from their website).</text></p></blockquote></p><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[Form 2  insrt Gaz 72 of 1 June 2007  Sch 1[68], effective 1 July 2007]</text></p></leg:histnote>
